rest_of_day_open: I envision the rest of my week going well. I've had several good weeks over the past month, and don't anticipate any significant change. I have been more active on many fronts and feel more in control of my life. Furthermore, there has been some positive news regarding COVID-19 vaccines and pending further stimulus payment updates.
critical_positive: We started off talking right away and there was no significant moments of pauses. The person I talked with was very friendly and talkative and provided a lot of information when I asked my questions. Likewise I also provided information of my own which kept our conversation going. We also shared similar interests which propelled the conversations along. I believed there was several topics we talked about, which we could have expanded on given more time.
critical_negative: I think the fact that we were on the clock made the conversation less natural. At the beginning of each conversation with a stranger there is some expected anxiety, and I did feel that at the beginning of this session. We also skimmed over many topics, some of which I would have liked to go into more in-depth.

rest_of_day_open: I am anticipating a relaxing weekend of gardening and reading. It looks like work this coming week will be busy, but I won't have to visit all of my offices, so I should be productive.  I am looking forward to evenings on my patio after work, since it will be cooler this week.  I'm just hoping it stays that way for a while!
critical_positive: I liked that Hua (sp?) had a plan going into the conversation. I can tend to be a little shy getting started, but he was very personable, and we actually ended up having a lot in common.  I felt like we had a good flow - neither of us dominated the conversation (there was good give and take), and the time flew by.
critical_negative: I worry that maybe I talked too much about the fact I have a therapist.  Is that weird?  But I am very open about mental health, and feel it shouldn't be stigmatized to have therapy. Also, since he is a professional in that field, it didn't seem out of line.  I can't think of anything else. Since Covid-19 has kept me indoors for the last few months, this was the first social conversation I've had with someone I don't know, and it was honestly delightful.
